7. soror, Octavia, the neglected wife of Antony. She died B.c. 11.

8. supplice vitta. The vitta was a ribbon worn round the head by matrons. A supplex vitta seems to be the same ribbon, twined with flocks of red and white wool (infula), and worn at festal sacrifices. The day was a supplicatio or ‘ thanksgiving. ’
